The paper discusses the evolution of communication networks and the need for signal processing research to enable data-driven statistical learning algorithms for distributed, robust, and online network operation and management. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for resilience and robustness to failures and malicious cyberattacks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of intelligent devices and statistical learning algorithms, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the construction of maps of the dynamic network state, which suggests that it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of large-scale heterogeneous networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
